Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Lay the @salmon fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle over a little @oil{}(a little), then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, roast the salmon on the top shelf until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a #medium saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring to a boil.

Add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

While the fish and noodles cook, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Slice the @sugar snap peas{80%g} in half lengthways.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the sugar snaps and stir-fry until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @coleslaw mix{120%g} and @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} to the sugar snaps. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds} more.

Stir in the @teriyaki sauce{50%g}, @hoisin sauce{64%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles to the sauce and veg, mixing together well so the noodles are coated in the sauce.

Share the noodles between your #bowls{} and top with the salmon.

Drizzle the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} over the salmon, then finish by sprinkling the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} over everything.

Enjoy!